'''''Star Wars'' 12''' is the twelfth issue of the [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] series [[Star Wars (1977)|''Star Wars'']]. It was written by [[Archie Goodwin]], illustrated by [[Carmine Infantino]] and [[Terry Austin]], and first published by [[Marvel Comics]] on [[March 14]], [[1978]]. It features the story "'''Doomworld!'''," in which [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and his [[Droid/Legends|droid]] companions find themselves stranded on the [[Waterworld/Legends|waterworld]] of [[Drexel/Legends|Drexel]].

==Publisher's summary==
''Luke is stranded on the water world Drexel and finds himself caught between two opposing forces each looking to possess his ship.''

==Plot summary==
{{Quote|<nowiki />''Whatever'' they are, Threepio, they're ''armed''&mdash;and ''opening fire'' on those sea monsters with ''us'' caught in the ''middle!''<nowiki />|Luke Skywalker|<ref name="Star Wars (1977) 12">[[Star Wars (1977) 12|''Star Wars'' (1977) 12]]</ref>}}
Luke Skywalker and the [[Droid/Legends|droids]] [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] are stranded on the [[Water/Legends|water]] world Drexel. While floating in their [[Escape pod/Legends|escape pod]], they are caught in the middle of a battle between the [[sea-dragon]]s, ridden by the [[Dragon Lords]], and the [[hydra craft]], [[Pilot/Legends|piloted]] by [[Governor/Legends|Governor]] [[Quarg]]'s men. The combatants are battling for the prize of Luke's wrecked ship, as anything mechanical is a rare commodity on the [[Ocean/Legends|ocean]]-covered [[Planet/Legends|planet]]. The battle ends in a standoff, but Luke and the droids are captured by the skimmer pilots and brought back to their base, where Luke tries to convince Quarg that the droids would be more useful to them intact than stripped down for parts.

Meanwhile, [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] is leading [[Crimson Jack/Legends|Crimson Jack]] and his gang of [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]] to the [[Drexel system/Legends|Drexel system]] under the pretense that there is treasure to be found, but the pirates become suspicious when they arrive and the only planet in the [[Star system/Legends|system]] is entirely covered in water.

